name: Card Pack
description: A pack of five (5) cards.

name: Tiab, the Kraken
description: Granted the title 'Hero of Oceanic Grove' for helping defeat The Ice King's army at Oceana Grove in Heavy Rain 20, year 403.Attack: Damages any card or player.Protect: Protects all allied cards.

name: Vendrick, Dragon of the North
description: The frostfire dragon Vendrick, friend of The Ice King. Vendrick helped The Ice King against the siege on Frostbite in Ash Season 27, year 412.Frostfire: Damages and freezes enemy card for 1 turn. Does not stack or reset.

name: Avehosa the Healer
description: Avehosa is renowned in her homeland as the woman who can cure all wounds, no matter how horrid they may be. Heal: Heals any card.

name: Mugosh the Ogre
description: Mugosh is the leader of a wild ogre clan, whom roam the land seemingly aimlessly.Attack: Damages any card or player.Taunt: Prevents damage to card's owner.

name: Wyther, the Venomous Snake
description: Intelligent serpent which kills its victims via its venom. She is at the peak of the food chain of the Plains Realm.Poison: Poisons any card. Stacks.

name: Skeletal Minion
description: A minion of Gavin's Army, brought back to life through necromancy.Attack: Damages any card or player.Taunt: Prevents damage to card's owner.

name: Gavin, the Undead King
description: One of the eldest of the undead! Gavin is ruler of Heartgard, one of three major factions in the underworld.Attack: Damages any card or player.Protect: Protects all allied cards.

name: Boago, the Wizard
description: An advisor to The Ice King's between Heavy Rain 29, year 402 - Crop 7. year 426. He was loyal to the end, sacrificed by the very king's he served.Attack: Damages any card or player.Spikes: Causes 1 recoil damage to any attacking card.

name: Fraycia, the Desert Elf
description: The Desert Elves are a race of females; with the exception of a male that born every 50 years. He becomes their king after taking the life of the previous ruler.Attack: Damages any card or player.Sandstorm: Passively damages every card on the field, at the start of every turn.

name: Lost Soul
description: Souls are collected through necromancy spells, long forgotten; or so the world thought.Souls: Grants 2 souls when played on the field, in exchange for 1 HP. Will not kill user.

name: Orshell, the Great Turtle
description: The Great Turtles are near-immortal beings, forever overseeing the eight realms. Neutral watchers, they avoid mortal quarrels.Sturdy: Cannot be killed in one blow.Protect: Protects all allied cards.

name: Scourgeblood the Spider
description: Scourgeblood is the current queen of spiders, of the Plains Realm. It it said that she is over 600 years old (and still young!), but no one really knows for sure.Attack: Damages any card or player.Poison: Poisons any card. Stacks.

name: Antidote
description: Purchased from the greatest apothecary of the Human Realm, servant of Human King Eluryh.Antidote: Cures all stacks of poison on any card.

name: Awaken
description: From the Realm of Dragons to our Human's vast plains, wherever there is light: there is hope.' - Eluryh, The King of HumansAwaken: Enables a used or newly summoned card.

name: Leyutu, the Skeletal Ancient
description: An ancient brought back to life through necromancy. Escaping it's summoner's captivity, it destroyed the city of Pyrestream in the Night Realm and remains there to this day.Attack: Damages any card or player.Screech: Lowers defense of an enemy card by 2.

name: Elnath, the Wise Mage
description: Counselor to the King of Humans until the King's death.Attack: Damages any card or player.Roar: Lowers attack of an enemy card by 2.

name: The Ice King
description: Because Vendrick took pity upon The Ice King Lineage on the siege on Frostbite of Ash Season 27, year 412, all descendants of The Ice King have dragon's blood running through their veins.Frostfire: Damages and freezes enemy card for 1 turn. Does not stack or reset.

name: Thili, the Pyromancer
description: A wanderer, Thili had become lost in the mountainous Ice Realm. Seconds from death, she discovered her unique talent for Pyromancy, thawing away all of the frost around her.Warmth: Thaws every frozen card, including enemy cards.

name: Melgorn, the Dwarf
description: Known for his spectacular mechanized exoskeletons, this dwarf is a high ranking official in the Mountain Realm parliament.Snipe: Any card summoned while this card is on the field will take 1 damage. Stacks.

name: Fire Fissure
description: Only cast by the oldest, most powerful mages during great wars. It is a last resort, reserved for the most desperate of circumstances.Fissure: Destroys all cards on both fields in exchange for 22 HP of the summoner.

name: Breiru, a Rithian Warrior
description: Rithian Warriors pledged allegiance to no nation. Wars were only fought in defense of their homeland.Attack: Damages any card or player.

name: Astyc, the Mad Witch
description: While still alive, Astyc was driven to insanity as she spent a century trapped in the Under Realm. She eventually escaped through a portal in the Night Realm.Attack: Damages any card or player.Mad Spell: When played, three separate spells are cast; each attacks the card with the highest HP for 1 damage, friend or foe.

name: Ifor, the Silent Assassin
description: Working for the highest bidder, Ifor was revered as the deadliest assassin throughout the human realm.Silence: Disables the use of any cards on the enemy's field for one turn. Can be canceled with Awaken.

name: Seduxia, the Manipulator
description: A Dwarf/Human hybrid. Seduxia amassed a following which quickly formed into a religion whose followers viewed her as a goddess.Capture: Brings an opponent's card into caster's control.

name: Gain, the Underestimated
description: A dragon from the east, Gain surprised his fellow kin by defeating a much larger foe after being backed into a corner.Attack: Damages any card or player.Hidden Potential: When HP is low, attack power doubles.

name: Aharitios, the Unsatisfied
description: A human man, so greedy, he was eventually cursed for his wrongdoings which transformed him into a lower level dragon. Even now, he guards his hoard.Greed: Draws two cards.

name: Deluge, Spirit of Flame
description: Unable to control its own power, this flame spirit will continue to grow until it burns itself out.Attack: Damages any card or player.Flame Surge: At the start of each turn, increase attack stat by one point without limit.

name: Soul Shot
description: A concentrated mass of souls, constructed by sheer willpower of it's caster. Soul Shot: Attacks the target card directly, dealing 4 damage.

name: Cyri, the Repulsive
description: Cyri, a filthy misunderstood blob, repels all who are near. A strong enough dosage of her stench is said to be enough to kill.Return: Returns the target card to the owner's hand. Costs half of the souls of the target card.

name: Khais, the Well
description: The undead king Gavin cursed Khais, and many of his kind, to be living excess Soul storage vessels during his war among the living. Reservoir: For each turn on the field the cost of this card increases by 1.Release: When destroyed, the cost of this card is converted into Souls and given to the owner.

name: The Wall
description: Serving the castle guard, The Wall protected the princess from Gavin during the attack on the human realm. Protect: Protects all allied cards.

name: Agrili, the Armorer
description: Infusing all armor with his magic, he was renouned as the best armorer in the Human Realm.Reinforce: Adds 1 defense to any card.

name: Zaaris, the Paranoid
description: After his unfortunate meeting with Gavin, the halfing used potions to stay alert for over 10 years before his death.Insomnia: Immediately awake on summon - even on the first turn. Cannot be put to sleep by any skill.Attack: Damages any card or player.

name: Solaen, the Thief
description: His greatest heist involved stealing the human king's crown right off his smug head. Patience: Bypasses any Taunt card.Attack: Damages any card or player.

name: Lozen, the Apothecary
description: After an ungrateful patient took both of his legs, the former doctor honed his dangerous knowledge. He created powerful poisons that killed thousands of men.Poison Gas: Poisons all cards on the enemy field. Stacks.

name: Veine, a Succubus
description: One of the demons which were summoned by Gavin, but later escaped after his defeat. Lifesteal: Gains additional health equal to damage done on each attack to cards or tomes.

name: Yaden, the Maestro
description: Harnessing her harp, she could cast music through the vibrations of the air itself. Dark Sound: When summoned, damages all enemy cards equal to this card's attack stat.Attack: Damages any card or player.

name: Dob, the Helper
description: Lower level demon which cannot act on it's own; it follows the will of the caster until death. Attack: Damages any card or player.Tag Along: When an ally attacks, this card jumps into action!

name: Soul Seed
description: By taking a small fragment of one's own soul, the caster can slowly corrupt another from the inside out.Soul Seed: After three turns, kills the target.

name: Faust, the Defense
description: Directly responsible for the upkeep of Gavin's undead army. Soul Shield: Protects allied cars from status effects such as Poison and Freeze.

name: Gwann, the Executioner
description: The Executioner had the ability to rip souls directly from a living being, an ability previously thought impossible.Sacrifice: Instantly destroys any card on the field. The remaining health of the target is removed from the caster's HP.

name: Celar, the Grinder
description: The King's butcher was known for his unique tenderizing abilities. Erosion: Damages any card or player. Each consecutive strike deals twice as much damage as the last.

name: Kasur, the Artist
description: Painted all of the portrait pieces in the grand tome.Reversal: Damages any card, using the target card's attack stat.

name: Trum, the Traitor
description: Put countless in danger of economic collapse after stealing from their own king's vault to pay off a debt. Hand Over: Moves a card from your field to the enemy field.

name: Clora, the Devoted
description: Season: Fade (FA) - A short spring-like period with warm nights. Only one of the two suns are visible around this time of the year.Toxic Burst: After 3 turns of existing (be it in hand or field) this card will explode, poisoning anything nearby.

name: Metan, the Enlightened
description: Uses a special powder to keep soldiers from slacking off. No one knows what it's made of.Enlighten: Awakens all cards on the summoner's field.

name: Gloon, the eldest Ranvan
description: Glohnn's brother. They look very alike. Managed to survive the sacrifice of Ryshire with the help of his brother.Summon Shield: Adds 99 defense when summoned. Decays next turn.Shield Decay: Decays summon shield after one turn.Protect: Protects all allied cards.

name: Glohnn, the younger Ranvan
description: Gloon's brother. They act very alike. Managed to keep his mouth shut for once.Summon Shield: Adds 99 defense when summoned. Decays next turn.Shield Decay: Decays summon shield after one turn.Taunt: Prevents damage to card's owner.

name: Siddry, the Ghost
description: A survivor from the attack on Drylake, Bright Sun 14 year 380.His mission: Destroy the young king Eluryh.Curse: Marks the card last attacked by this one.Promise: On death, destroys all marked cards.

name: Drip, the Original
description: His powers awakened during the Siege of Frostbite - Ash Season 27, year 412 - in a failed attempt to save loved ones.Copy: Copies attack, health, defense, and skill of the last living summoned card.:

name: Comor, the Unique
description: Ash Season of 412, the Human King Eluryh called upon all halfing soldiers with unique abilities to help him defend Frostbite.Soul Charge: Grants the summoner 1 soul each turn this card is in their field.Taunt: Prevents damage to card's owner.

name: Mort, the Cursed
description: All mortal beings that inhaled Gavin's mist were cursed, quickly dying. However, a handful managed to escape death and even gain power from the curse inflicted upon them.Attack: Damages any card or player.Curse Mark: When the targeted card is destroyed, add 1 to every attack, defense, and health.

name: Grue, the Wise
description: Monks residing in the Oceanic Grove were known for their ability to actually increase their power over the course of a battle.Attack: Damages any card or player.Damage Recall: When damaged, add 1 attack and defense to this card.

name: Zengu, the Undying
description: An ogre of The Night Realm, Zengu was one of the 13 directly responsible for Gavin's resurrection of Ash Season year 487.Attack: Damages any card or player.Skeleton Resurrection: When an ally card falls, an ally skeleton minion will be summoned.

name: Bone
description: The Human King used his army of mechanization powered men to attack the city of Drylake. The Desert King did not take this attack lightly; what followed was an all out war between the humans and elves of the desert. - Bright Sun 14, year 380Bone: When three bones are on the same field, they will combine into a single Skeleton Minion at the start of their turn.

name: Vamar, the Fragmented
description: Following his fathers untimely death, the then young Eluryh, King of Humans, ordered troops to attack the Desert Realm. - Bright Sun 14, year 380Attack: Damages any card or player.Bone Slinger: When used, this card will leave behind a bone on the enemy field.

name: Siadric, the Ready
description: The ogre of the Night Realm had long been conspiring against the Human King, Eluryh. Furious about how he and the humans has treated the ogres of the Plains Realm, the Night Realm ogres had spent twenty years preparing for an attack on the Human RealmAttack: Damages any card or player.Offense Boost: When attacked, damage done is added to the attack stat of this card.

name: Soril, the Savage
description: A deafening sound that could be heard across the entire common world and beyond. A chill went down the spine of every living being on the planet; Gavin walks the world once more. - Ash Season 12, 487Attack: Damages any card or player.Soul Absorption: When this card is on the field, any spent souls from it's owner add to this card's attack.

name: Fyr of Heaven
description: The elven, without their king, quickly fell on their knees to Gavin. With their old king in stasis, no new heir could take the throne. - Ash Season 12, 487Taunt: Prevents damage to card's owner.Gather: When this card is on the field, any spent souls from it's owner add to this card's health.

name: Ralith, the Creator
description: The ogre of the Night Realm sacrificed the human city of Ryshire to summon the Undead King, Gavin - Ash Season 11, year 487.Protect: Protects all allied cards.Congregation: When this card is on the field, any card added to the field will give the owner 1 soul.

name: Kark, the Selfish
description: Many speculated that the curse would end - maybe Gavin would be their true god and save them from the many grievances caused by their gods of old. - Ash Season 11, year 487.Attack: Damages any card or player.Self Alleviation: Heals this card by 1 if it is below it's base HP at the start of the owner's turn.

description: A curse was placed upon those who dared to challenge the Ice King - causing them to burst into frost, damaging their forces. - Ash Season 27, year 412.Attack: Damages any card or player.Absolute Zero: On death, freeze's the opponent's field.

description: Gavin had a lust for power that would eventually drive the entire race of elves extinct, once and for all. - Ash Season 11, year 487.Protect: Protects all allied cards.Toxic Blast: On death, poisons the attacker's field. Stacks.
